'''Alejandro J. Lacayo Baca''' Born in [[Nicaragua]] August 9, 1951. Attended College at [[Georgetown University]], [[Washington D.C.]] 1969/1973 Mr Alejandro J. Lacayo is currently Honorary Consul of Portugal in Nicaragua from June 2018, and Malaysia Honorary Consul in Nicaragua, accredited by the Government of Nicaragua by Presidential decree No 20-2017, His father Alejandro Lacayo Montealegre founded the [[Monte Rosa Sugar Mill]] in Nicaragua. Alejandro J. Lacayo is currently a business man in Nicaragua growing [[coffee]] and [[sugar cane]]. He is also involved in Corporate Advisory for infrastructure projects and distribution logistics for Foreign Companies. Mr. Lacayo played [[golf]] for the Nicaraguan National Amateur Seniors Team, competing annually in [[Central America]]. Mr. Lacayo in 2009 was appointed as Honorary Consul General of the '''[[Republic of India]]''' in Nicaragua. https://web.archive.org/web/20080911172958/http://www.cancilleria.gob.ni/ see Diplomatic and Consular missions accredited in Nicaragua at the Foreign Ministry web page. See also '''India guide to Business in Latin America ''' http://www.businesswithlatinamerica.com/Contacts2.html and '''India Embassies in Latin America''' http://www.indembarg.org.ar/en/Indian%20embassies%20in%20LA.html, newspaper article El Nuevodiario http://www.elnuevodiario.com.ni/politica/40521, '''Ministry of external Affairs Government of India, official web page''' http://www.mea.gov.in/indian-mission.htm?159/Nicaragua
