'''Bosa Togs''' is a senior IT manager from [[Papua New Guinea]]. In 2016 she won the Westpac Outstanding Woman of the Year Award and the PricewaterhouseCoopers Private Sector Award.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://pacificwomeninbusiness.com.au/blog/inspiration/2016-westpac-outstanding-women-wow-award-winner-announced/|title=2016 Westpac Outstanding Women (WOW) Award winner announced - Pacific Women in Business|work=Pacific Women in Business|access-date=2018-07-14|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.looppng.com/content/women-leaders-urged-mentor-others|title=Women leaders urged to mentor others {{!}} Loop PNG|last=|first=|date=2016-11-11|work=Loop PNG|access-date=2018-07-14|language=en}}</ref>

Togs is the general manager for IT at Telikom Papua New Guinea. She successfully campaigned within the company for [[Equal pay for equal work|equal pay]] for women employed by Telikom, resulting in a change in remuneration policy by the corporation.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2016-10-24/papua-new-guinea-women-recognised-for-business-achievements/7958590|title=PNG women recognised for business achievements|date=2016-10-24|work=ABC News|access-date=2018-07-14|language=en-AU}}</ref>

She holds two masters degrees, one in IT and one in business administration.<ref name=":0" />  

