{{Infobox award | name = EFQM Global Excellence Award | subheader = | current_awards = | image = EFQM Award 2012.JPG | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | description = It recognises industry leaders with an indisputable track record of success in turning strategy into action and continuously improving their organisation's performance. | sponsor = [[EFQM]] | date = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location = [[Brussels|Brussels, Belgium]] | country = [[Europe]] | presenter = | host = | preshow_host = | acts = | reward = | year = 1992 | year2 = | holder = | website = {{URL|http://www.efqm.org/what-we-do/recognition/efqm-global-excellence-award}} }} The '''EFQM Excellence Award''' is a [[List of national quality awards|transnational quality award]] that recognises European businesses with "excellent and sustainable results" across all areas of the [[EFQM Excellence Model]].<ref>[https://www.researchgate.net/publication/228599823_The_EFQM_excellence_model_European_and_Dutch_experiences_with_the_EFQM_approach_in_health_care The EFQM excellence model: European and Dutch experiences with the EFQM approach in health care]</ref><ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.3846/13923730.2013.843582 | volume=20 | title=EFQM excellence model as the TQM model of the construction industry of southeastern Europe | year=2014 | journal=Journal of Civil Engineering and Management | pages=70–81 | last1 = Vukomanovic | first1 = Mladen | last2 = Radujkovic | first2 = Mladen | last3 = Marija Nahod | first3 = Maja}}</ref> It was established in October 1991 as the [[European Quality Award]] by the European Foundation for Quality Management ([[EFQM]]).<ref>{{Citation | last = Evans | first = James R | last2 = Lindsay | first2 = William M | year = 1999 | title = The Management and Control of Quality | chapter = 4: Managing for Quality and High Performance | edition = 4 | publisher = South-Western College Publishing | publication-place = [[Cincinnati|Cincinnati, Ohio]] | pages = 143–144 | isbn = 9780538882422 | oclc = 38475486}}</ref> The assessment process is one of the most robust of any award, with a team of independent assessors spending an average of 500 hours per applicant reviewing documentation and conducting interviews on-site.<ref>[http://www.zawya.com/mena/en/story/ZAWYA20160615090848/ Sharjah Chamber of Commerce and Industry introduces the Sharjah Top 10 Business Award]</ref>{{failed verification|date=October 2016}}
== Award Categories == The Award is open to organisations from both the Private and Public Sectors. Applicants will either be recognized as "Finalists", "Prize Winners" or "Award Winners". An "Award Winner" is an organisation that is able to demonstrate that they are considered a role model for the Fundamental Concepts of Excellence, as defined in the [[EFQM Excellence Model]].<ref>[http://www.infocalidad.net/archives/noticia/el-madrileno-ayuntamiento-de-alcobendas-nominado-al-efqm-excellence-award-2016 El madrileño Ayuntamiento de Alcobendas, nominado al EFQM Excellence Award 2016]</ref><ref>[http://www.automobil-produktion.de/technik-produktion/produktionstechnik/efqm-excellence-award-fuer-bmw-regensburg-257.html EFQM Excellence Award für BMW Regensburg]</ref><ref>[http://www.constructionweekonline.com/article-39313-qatar-rail-becomes-full-member-of-efqm/ Qatar Rail becomes full member of EFQM]</ref><ref>[http://www.arabianaerospace.aero/emirates-group-security-awarded-the-dubai-quality-award.html Emirates Group Security awarded the Dubai Quality Award]</ref><ref>[http://www.advertiser.ie/galway/article/37141/galway-bay-hotel-wins-prestigious-efqm-excellence-award Galway Bay Hotel wins prestigious EFQM Excellence award]</ref> There are 4 categories:
1. Large Private Sector (over 1000 employees)
2. Small / Medium Private Sector (less than 1000 employees)
3. Large Public Sector (over 1000 employees)
4. Small / Medium Public Sector (less than 1000 employees)
An independent jury of experts review the applications and the reports from the assessments. Each year, they can decide to give multiple awards, in line with the Award Categories. The last time there were multiple winners was 2008, when [[BMW]] won in the Large Private Sector category and St. Mary's College won in the Small / Medium Public Sector category. However, if no organisation can adequately demonstrate they are a role model, they can decide there is no Award Winner that year. This last happened in 2010.{{citation needed|date=September 2016}}
