{{Infobox settlement | name = Silicon Hills | native_name = [[Greater Austin]] | native_name_lang = <!-- ISO 639-2 code e.g. "fr" for French. If more than one, use {{lang}} instead --> | settlement_type = [[List of technology centers|Tech hub]] | image_skyline = Silicon_Hills.jpeg | image_map = Austin MSA.png | image_size = 300px | image_caption = | etymology = | nickname = | coordinates = | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = [[United States]] | subdivision_type1 = State | subdivision_name1 = [[Texas]] | subdivision_type2 = City | subdivision_name2 = [[Austin, Texas|Austin]] | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''Silicon Hills''' is a nickname for the cluster of high-tech companies in the [[Austin, Texas|Austin]] metropolitan area in the [[U.S. state]] of [[Texas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://boss.blogs.nytimes.com/2013/07/17/austins-silicon-hills-builds-on-its-infrastructure/|title=Austin's 'Silicon Hills' Builds on Its Infrastructure|first=Eilene|last=Zimmerman|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Williams|first1=Sarah|title=Could Austin — the ‘Silicon Hills’ of Texas — become the next biotech hub?|url=https://www.statnews.com/2016/03/09/austin-texas-biotech-industry/|website=STAT news|publisher=STAT|accessdate=29 June 2016}}</ref> The name is analogous to [[Silicon Valley]], but refers to the [[Texas Hill Country|hilly terrain on the west side of Austin]]. High tech industries in the area include [[enterprise software]], [[semiconductors]], [[Research and development|corporate R&D]], [[biotechnology]], [[video game industry|gaming]], and a variety of [[startup company|startup companies]].
Technology companies with offices in the area include [[Advanced Micro Devices]], [[Apple Inc.]], [[ARM Holdings]], [[Cisco]], [[eBay]], [[Facebook]], [[Google]], [[IBM]], [[Indeed]], [[Intel]], [[Silicon Labs]], [[Texas Instruments]], [[Oracle Corporation]], [[VMWare]], and [[List of companies based in Austin, Texas|many others]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.builtinaustin.com/2016/10/01/Austin-top-100|title=The Top 100 Digital Tech Employers in Austin|publisher=}}</ref> [[Dell]]'s worldwide [[headquarters]] are located in [[Round Rock, Texas|Round Rock]], a [[suburb]] of Austin.
==Venture capital and incubators== Austin was one of the top areas for venture capital with investors investing $621 million in 2013 (43% of that went to software and semiconductor firms). Some [[venture capital]] investors include [[Austin Ventures]], Central Texas [[Angel investor|Angels]] Network, and Tritium Partners.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.builtinaustin.com/2016/03/30/austin-venture-capital-firms-every-entrepreneur-should-know|title=Austin venture capital firms every entrepreneur should know|publisher=}}</ref> There are at least 15 [[startup incubator]]s as well, including: [[Capital Factory]], Austin [[Business incubator|Technology Incubator]], and the IC<sup>''2''</sup> Institute<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ic2.utexas.edu/|title=IC² Institute, The University of Texas at Austin - Innovation, Creativity, Capital|publisher=}}</ref> (the incubator for the [[University of Texas at Austin]]).
